It didn’t help the situation that Calvin and Jessie were running late to the airport, since Jessie had already been fuming at Calvin and preparing to end the relationship with him.

0.22: Upon arriving at their terminal, they had only 45 minutes until their international flight would depart from Jamaica for the US.

0.06: It had been a tough vacation, which was planned well before Jessie began to think of breaking up with Calvin 6 weeks ago.  

0.11: Calvin knew that Jessie was upset, but wasn't sure what to do besides attempt to carry on as normal.

****** LOCATION BOUNDARY ******

0.44: The security line was very short, and once the online boarding passes were scanned, they put their bags on the conveyor belt.

0.0: Calvin also took off his belt and watch.

0.11: There was a short halt in security proceedings so that the security guards could change shifts, but, once everything was back in order, they were ushered quickly through the metal detector. 

0.33: “The infrastructure of this airport is really quite poor," said Calvin as they waited for their bags to emerge from the x-ray machine.

0.11: “I could've hidden something in my shoes easily.” 

0.11: Jessie, exasperated, scowled at the conveyor belt.

0.06: “What?” he asked.

****** SOCIAL BOUNDARY ******

0.56*: Balling up her fists and turning to him angrily, she said, “Calvin, I want to break up because I don’t think our personalities are compatible. 

0.06: I think it’s best that once we get to the States we part ways for good.” 

****** LOCATION BOUNDARY ******

0.0: Calvin said nothing as he grabbed his bag and walked down the concourse.

0.33: Jessie trailed behind him as they hurried their way quickly toward gate A28.

0.17: “So now you have nothing to say?” Jessie asked. 

0.0: Calvin didn't answer, gritting his teeth and staring straight ahead. 

0.22: He was very frustrated that he felt he had been trying to appease Jessie for the entirety of the vacation, and it seemed to be completely unappreciated. 

0.11: Their silence was punctuated only by the rapid, rhythmic clacking of their suitcase wheels over the tile floor as they continued power-walking through the terminal. 

****** SOCIAL BOUNDARY ******

0.28: Calvin finally turned to address her as they continued walking: “Jessie, this makes perfect sense. 

0.06: If you feel this way, then I think we should break up because I don’t want to keep boring you.

0.0: I agree, let’s part ways once we make it back.

0.11: You should’ve spoken up about my apparent intolerability before you decided to plan this vacation.”

0.06: He was very hurt, even though he didn’t want to show it. 

****** LOCATION BOUNDARY ******

0.56*: Having made it to their gate, they scanned their tickets, and the annoyed flight attendant shooed them onto the plane and then closed the plane door behind them.

0.0: Luckily, they had forgotten to arrange seats next to each other on the flight back.

0.06: They were both in economy, but Jessie was headed for seat 33A while Calvin's seat was 36F. 

****** SOCIAL BOUNDARY ******

0.28: Before Jessie sat down, she took a deep breath, calmed her emotions, and then awkwardly shook Calvin’s hand, mumbling, “Have a nice flight. 

0.17: Oh, and when you get a chance, could you send me back all the philosophy books I lent you?”

0.06: He laughed in disbelief and walked to his window seat three rows back to get ready for takeoff.

0.06: Both were upset but glad that they would have this flight in solitude.

